data.title: Pro Football Hall of Fame Class of 1973
meta_keywords: best football players of all time
data.meta_description: The Pro Football Hall of Fame Class of 1973 - Future Football Legends
data.text:
The 3-member Pro Football Hall of Fame Class of 1973 was highlighted by the enshrinements of Jim Parker and Raymond Berry.

Notable players who didn't make the final cut this year were Roosevelt "Rosey" Brown and Lou Groza (see below for the rest of the finalists).

The Enshrinement Ceremony was held on Saturday, July 28th, 1973.
